RACE.RACE_TEXT: Commonwealth Turf S. CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 11 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 109. Stakes Purse 300000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIGANTE prompted between the leaders before easing back from tight quarters into the first turn, stalked the embattled leading trio from the two to three path, split them to take aim from the four path entering the lane, bid in upper stretch and drove clear. NORTHERN INVADER broke a step slow, trailed in the two path, gained in the four path around the far turn, shifted to the five path entering the lane, but leveled off in upper stretch, sustained stride to bid for place in the final sixteenth and reeled in that position at the wire. SMOKEY MANDATE vied for the lead inside of a pair of rivals, led entering the lane, but was bested by an outer foe in midstretch, dug in for place in the final sixteenth but was nailed at the wire. WINTERS LION laid off of the pace along the inside, was urged along towards the rear in the three to four path around the far turn, then moved up. LINCOLN HIGHWAY brushed with an outer rival at the start, laid off of the pace in the three path, came under urging around the far turn and failed to menace. WILD SEAN brushed with an inner foe at the start, vied two wide and between horses, entered the lane in the three path but faded. WORTHINGTON steadied out of tight quarters into the first turn, pursued along the inside and faded around the far turn. J. P. RACE vied three wide then weakened entering the lane in the five path.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 12 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 120000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $50,000 In Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOURBON TO BLAME broke outwardly, prompted two wide and drew clear entering the lane. MISINTENTION laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, fanned to the six path entering the lane and rallied. RITA'S ONTHE BEACH saved ground off of the pace, offered a rail grind to vie for place coming to midstretch, but was outkicked then saved show. LISA'S NONNO broke a step slow, raced at the rear in the six to seven path and ran on. VICTORIOUS broke inwardly, set the pace inside of a pressing foe, was bested entering the lane and gave way between horses. FAST N HAPPY bumped with an outer rival at the start, pursued from midpack along the inside inched closer in the four path around the turn but flattened out between horses. RUBIA tracked in the two path and lacked a bid. BEAUTIFUL BOLT tracked four wide but faded between horses at the three furlong pole. A DOLLAR A DAY lacked speed in the four path into the turn and was outrun. MISSILE bumped with an inner rival at the start, stalked three wide then weakened between horses. JOHANNY pursued from the five path, but was pulled up around the turn and got vanned off.
